bilingual.source: The premium I pay every month is high.
bilingual.target: 我每个月支付的保险费很高。

bilingual.source: The premium for this insurance plan is cheap.
bilingual.target: 这个保险计划的保险费很便宜。

bilingual.source: We need to compare the premium from different companies.
bilingual.target: 我们需要比较不同公司的保险费。

bilingual.source: Do you know how much your car premium is?
bilingual.target: 你知道你的汽车保险费是多少吗？

bilingual.source: They decided to increase the health premium.
bilingual.target: 他们决定增加健康保险费。

bilingual.source: OK. How will the premium be paid?
bilingual.target: 好吧怎么支付保险费呢?。

bilingual.source: Could you grant me a premium rebate?
bilingual.target: 你能给我保险费折扣吗?。

yingyinNormal.en: And I'll pass on a glass of that non-premium liquor that you're drinking.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我可不想要你正在喝的廉价酒精。

yingyinNormal.en: Customers have to pay a premium to make up for the cost of installing the technology.
yingyinNormal.zh: 居民要花额外费用引进技术。

yingyinNormal.en: Penny laid into me, too. Apparently, I'm overly fixated on premium Swiss chocolate bars.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩妮也把我骂了一顿。显然，我过分专注在优质的瑞士巧克力棒上。

yingyinNormal.en: I can get a rider to your homeowner's policy, and just split the increase in your premium?
yingyinNormal.zh: 我可以在你房屋保险上附个合同，分用你保险金的溢价，怎么样？

yingyinNormal.en: Nips put a premium on shooting medics. That white's a bull's eye. Here, I got you a new helmet. One size fits all.
yingyinNormal.zh: 小日本极好枪击军医。那白色的靶心。拿去，我给你个新头盔。一码配所有。

yingyinNormal.en: Hong Kong truly is a vertical city. Because of its geography, space is at a premium which means it has one of the highest population densities in the world.
yingyinNormal.zh: 香港的确是一个垂直城市。由于其地理条件，香港的空间十分宝贵，这意味着香港的人口密度在全球名列前茅。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: The egg industry's push is the first major test of whether animal products from regenerative farms can become the next <highlight>premium</highlight> offering.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 蛋业的推动是对再生农场的动物产品能否成为下一个优质产品的首次重大考验。

examination_example.sentence: The industry is betting that the same consumers paying more for <highlight>premium</highlight> attributes such as free-range, non-GMO, and pasture-raised eggs will embrace sustainability.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 该行业正在押注，花更多钱为自由放养、非转基因和牧场饲养等优质属性的鸡蛋买单的消费者，也将同样地接受可持续性。

examination_example.sentence: Insurance companies, meanwhile, can base their <highlight>premiums</highlight> on AI models that more accurately access risk.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 与此同时，保险公司可以根据能更准确评估风险的人工智能模型来计算保费。

sense_info_list.zh: (put a premium on)奖励; 重视; 鼓励

examination_example.sentence: To combat the trap of putting a <highlight>premium</highlight> on being busy, Cal Newport recommends building a habit of "deep work".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为避免陷入“重视忙碌”的陷阱，卡尔·纽坡特建议养成“深度工作”的习惯。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: the amount by which the price of a share or other security exceeds its issue price, its nominal value, or the value of the assets it represents

examination_example.sentence: Higher prices, called price <highlight>premiums</highlight>, can be justified as a way to compensate farmers for providing ecosystem services.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 较高的价格，又被称作价格溢价，可以作为补偿农民提供生态系统服务的一种方式。

examination_example.sentence: But a look at the prices on online grocer Fresh Direct suggests a grass-fed <highlight>premium</highlight> of anywhere from 35-60%.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但看一眼在线食品杂货商生鲜直达的价目就会发现，草饲产品的溢价在35-60%之间。

examination_example.sentence: Consumers could pay a <highlight>premium</highlight> of 30-50% or more for grass-fed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 消费者有可能要为草饲产品支付30-50%甚至更高的溢价。

examination_example.sentence: In the end, the amount paid for <highlight>premiums</highlight> is about the same.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最后，支付的保费金额大致相同。

examination_example.sentence: Americans are deeply concerned about the relentless rise in health care costs and health insurance <highlight>premiums</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 美国人对日益高昂的医疗费用和医疗保险费深感担忧。

examination_example.sentence: Malpractice awards do drive up insurance <highlight>premiums</highlight> for doctors in high-risk specialties.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 医疗事故赔偿确实提高了高风险专业医生的保险费。
